  "prompt": "How can you avoid a girl who has a huge crush on you without hurting her?",
  "response": "Avoiding someone who has a crush on you while minimizing hurt requires sensitivity, honesty, and respect. Here are some steps to handle the situation gently:\n\n1. **Be Honest, but Kind**:  \n   - If the girl expresses her feelings, acknowledge them respectfully without encouraging false hope.  \n   - Use gentle language, such as, \u201cI really appreciate your feelings, but I don\u2019t see us in that way.\u201d  \n\n2. **Set Boundaries**:  \n   - Politely but firmly establish boundaries to avoid mixed signals.  \n   - For example, if she tries to spend time with you one-on-one, suggest group activities instead.  \n\n3. **Limit Contact**:  \n   - Gradually reduce the amount of time you spend together or the frequency of your interactions.  \n   - Avoid situations where she might misinterpret your actions as romantic interest.  \n\n4. **Be Consistent**:  \n   - Don\u2019t send mixed messages (e.g., flirtatious behavior or overly friendly gestures).  \n   - Consistency will help her understand your intentions clearly.  \n\n5. **Respect Her Feelings**:  \n   - Avoid gossiping or making fun of her crush with others.  \n   - Treat her feelings with dignity, even if you don\u2019t reciprocate them.  \n\n6. **Focus on Friendship (If Appropriate)**:  \n   - If you want to remain friends, make it clear that your relationship is strictly platonic.  \n   - Be mindful that she may need time and space to process her feelings before resuming a friendship.  \n\n7. **Give Her Space**:  \n   - Sometimes, stepping back is the kindest thing you can do to allow her to move on.  \n   - Encourage her to focus on her own interests and goals.  \n\n8. **Be Patient**:  \n   - Understand that it might take time for her to accept your feelings (or lack thereof).  \n   - Avoid being harsh or impatient with her emotions.  \n\nRemember, it\u2019s impossible to completely avoid hurting someone\u2019s feelings, but being kind, honest, and respectful can help soften the impact.",
